FBIS4-13333 "drnes076_c_94009" FBIS-NES-94-076 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 Egypt Four `Extremists' Surrender in Asyut Four `Extremists' Surrender in Asyut NC1904210394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1525 GMT 19 Apr 94 NC1904210394 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Text] Asyut, 19 Apr (MENA)--Four members of terrorist groups have declared their repentance and decided to return to the right path after having been misled by extremist leaders. They declared their acceptance of the judicial verdicts in the cases in which they were implicated. Stating this, Asyut Governor Samih al-Sa'id added that the four extremists surrendered to the popular departments in the governorate today of their own volition and were handed over to the competent security agencies.
